</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="196" pageNumber="475" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="196.[794,1388,1090,1512]" lastBlockId="196.[179,1385,1518,1985]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[795,1053,1365,1394]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 100 mm, tail 89 mm, ear 15-6 mm, hindfoot 22-8 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Arguedas’s Grass Mouse is a medium-sized species of 
<taxonomicName box="[580,679,1518,1551]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="196" pageNumber="475" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Akodon</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum is brownish olive, contrasting with smoky gray to whitish venter; fur has hairs with paler gray bases; and tail is dark and moderately countershaded. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 22, FN = 40.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[181,1028,1640,1669]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="196.[179,1385,1518,1985]" box="[181,1028,1640,1669]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,292,1640,1669]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">Habitat.</emphasis>
Montane cloud forest at elevations of 2900-3800 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="196" pageNumber="475" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="196.[179,1385,1518,1985]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,447,1680,1709]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
Arguedas’s Grass Mouse is insectivorous and primarily eats adult beetles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
